WEBVTT

00:01.784 --> 00:03.307
DR. ANDREWS: Previously
onThe Good Doctor...

00:03.481 --> 00:05.222
Can I help you?My name's Miles Browne.
I'm your father.

00:05.396 --> 00:06.310
Go home.Whoa.

00:06.484 --> 00:08.095
I think
you're having a stroke.

00:08.269 --> 00:09.748
I have terminal cancer.

00:09.922 --> 00:12.316
I waited for you,
and you left.

00:12.490 --> 00:14.492
MILES: I thought about you
every day.

00:14.666 --> 00:16.016
♪♪♪♪

00:18.061 --> 00:19.019
It's good we're not
roommates anymore.

00:19.193 --> 00:20.368
'Cause
I couldn't do this.

00:22.065 --> 00:24.111
Having sex
doesn't make us a thing.

00:24.285 --> 00:25.503
You need to see
other women.

00:25.677 --> 00:27.331
Why? I don't
really want to...No excuses.

00:27.505 --> 00:29.377
You wanna come back
to my place for a little more?

00:29.551 --> 00:31.335
Just sleeping with you
isn't good for me.

00:31.509 --> 00:32.423
I want to give Heather
a chance.

00:35.035 --> 00:36.166
[WATER RUNNING]

00:36.340 --> 00:37.820
Thanks for cooking.Mm-hmm.

00:37.994 --> 00:39.517
And the new skillet.

00:39.691 --> 00:40.823
The chicken
was delicious.

00:40.997 --> 00:42.216
What'd I tell you?

00:42.390 --> 00:44.392
Cast iron kicks ass.

00:44.566 --> 00:45.741
Wait till you sear
a steak in it.

00:45.915 --> 00:47.264
You won't believe
the difference.

00:47.438 --> 00:48.570
I'll definitely try it.

00:48.744 --> 00:49.440
Mm.

00:51.181 --> 00:52.922
So, you up for a movie?

00:53.096 --> 00:56.012
Actually, I thought maybe
we could just talk.

00:58.014 --> 01:00.364
Oh. We've spent
all night talking.

01:00.538 --> 01:03.976
Yeah, about our jobs,
the news, the weather,

01:04.151 --> 01:05.108
but...

01:06.370 --> 01:08.155
We, uh...

01:08.329 --> 01:09.634
We never really
talked about the past.

01:11.027 --> 01:12.768
Oh, we did.

01:12.942 --> 01:14.378
When you were
in the hospital.

01:14.552 --> 01:15.510
Barely.

01:18.078 --> 01:20.167
Have you forgiven me?

01:20.341 --> 01:22.125
♪♪♪♪

01:26.738 --> 01:27.870
[SIGHS]

01:28.044 --> 01:29.567
I...

01:29.741 --> 01:31.613
I'd rather
just watch a movie.

01:31.787 --> 01:33.180
Claire, I don't...If you want to join, great.

01:33.354 --> 01:35.660
If not, let's just
call it a night.

01:38.315 --> 01:40.143
Okay. Movie it is.

01:41.013 --> 01:42.102
Okay.

01:42.276 --> 01:44.278
♪♪♪♪

01:48.760 --> 01:50.849
How'd your
presentation go?

01:51.023 --> 01:53.156
It was long.

01:55.245 --> 01:57.073
Didn't you do laundry
yesterday?

01:57.247 --> 01:58.944
I'm not doing laundry.
I'm packing.

01:59.119 --> 02:01.033
For our camping trip.

02:01.208 --> 02:03.079
We've done nothing but work
for three weeks,

02:03.253 --> 02:04.689
and neither of us feels...

02:04.863 --> 02:05.864
Better.

02:06.038 --> 02:08.128
A weekend in the woods

02:08.302 --> 02:10.260
isn't going to
change anything,

02:10.434 --> 02:12.262
not to mention you can't even
sleep on a couch,

02:12.436 --> 02:13.655
much less outside
on the ground.

02:13.829 --> 02:16.048
I agree.

02:16.223 --> 02:19.661
It's going to be a challenge,
but that's the point.

02:19.835 --> 02:22.490
The further outside
our comfort zones we go,

02:22.664 --> 02:23.317
the more distracted
we'll be.

02:23.491 --> 02:25.449
♪♪♪♪

02:30.541 --> 02:33.675
[KEYS RATTLE]

02:33.849 --> 02:37.853
[DOOR UNLOCKS]

02:38.027 --> 02:41.465
[ALARM BLARING]

02:41.639 --> 02:42.466
[BUTTONS BEEPING]

02:42.640 --> 02:44.033
[BUZZER]

02:44.207 --> 02:45.165
[BUTTONS BEEPING]

02:45.339 --> 02:46.383
[BUZZER]

02:47.602 --> 02:48.777
[BUTTONS BEEPING]

02:48.951 --> 02:49.821
[ALARM STOPS]

02:52.563 --> 02:53.912
Whoa!

02:54.086 --> 02:55.653
It's me!
It's me, okay?

02:55.827 --> 02:57.307
Don't shoot.Are you okay?

02:57.481 --> 02:58.787
I'm fine. Can you put
the gun down, please?

03:00.745 --> 03:02.269
I opened the door,
and the alarm went off.

03:02.443 --> 03:03.226
It's broken.

03:03.400 --> 03:04.706
Oh, thank God.

03:04.880 --> 03:06.577
Man.I thought somebody, uh...

03:07.839 --> 03:08.536
Hi.

03:10.015 --> 03:10.799
Hi.

03:16.587 --> 03:17.240
It's not loaded.

03:19.895 --> 03:20.939
Yeah. Good.

03:21.113 --> 03:22.724
No. No, not good.

03:22.898 --> 03:25.988
I store this
loaded always.

03:26.162 --> 03:28.512
I unloaded it.

03:28.686 --> 03:31.776
For this exact reason.
You could've killed me.

03:31.950 --> 03:34.301
And if you had
been an intruder,
you could've killed me.

03:34.475 --> 03:36.259
I'm not an intruder. I'm me.

03:36.433 --> 03:37.826
Hello?

03:38.000 --> 03:39.871
You had the gun pointed
right at my head.

03:40.045 --> 03:42.309
No. I was aiming
center mass.

03:42.483 --> 03:44.006
My finger wasn't even
on the trigger.

03:44.180 --> 03:45.225
Thank you very much
for the apology.

03:45.399 --> 03:46.313
Really appreciate it.

03:46.487 --> 03:48.097
Apology?

03:48.271 --> 03:50.491
What in the world
would make you think

03:50.665 --> 03:53.972
that it was okay
to unload my gun?

03:54.146 --> 03:57.324
You almost shot me
center mass, okay?

03:57.498 --> 03:58.977
But by all means,
don't apologize!

03:59.151 --> 04:01.415
I did not
almost shoot you,

04:01.589 --> 04:02.807
and if you don't stop
with the apology cr...

04:04.331 --> 04:05.245
I'm going to bed.

04:06.376 --> 04:07.508
Alone.

04:11.947 --> 04:13.644
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

04:23.045 --> 04:24.829
ASHER: The discoloration is a
deeper red than her last exam.

04:26.831 --> 04:28.311
CLAIRE: And it's warm
to the touch.

04:28.485 --> 04:29.486
Ow!

04:29.660 --> 04:31.619
Sorry. How long has it
been tender?

04:31.793 --> 04:34.578
Uh... About a week.

04:34.752 --> 04:36.798
Well, it's not a bruise
or muscle strain.

04:36.972 --> 04:39.453
The AV malformation's
growing.

04:39.627 --> 04:42.499
Which is why I've been
recommending surgery
since she was five.

04:42.673 --> 04:44.762
And I've agreed
every time.

04:44.936 --> 04:46.677
It's the first time
there's been any pain.

04:46.851 --> 04:49.158
And the meds and the
nutritional supplements
have been working.

04:49.332 --> 04:50.464
No, they haven't,

04:50.638 --> 04:53.162
and puberty will accelerate
the growth even more,

04:53.336 --> 04:56.121
which puts her at a high risk
for a spontaneous hemorrhage.

04:56.296 --> 04:58.559
Turtleneck sweaters
are definitely not
the solution any longer.

04:58.733 --> 04:59.560
She needs the surgery.

05:03.912 --> 05:05.435
When?

05:05.609 --> 05:06.871
We can admit her
and start the prep right now.

05:09.004 --> 05:09.874
AVA: Awesome.

05:12.703 --> 05:13.356
I hate turtlenecks.

05:16.838 --> 05:18.535
Your EKG's normal,
cholesterol's low,

05:18.709 --> 05:20.145
and I didn't see
any concerning moles.

05:20.320 --> 05:21.364
I wear SPF 50 every day.

05:22.713 --> 05:24.802
There was one thing.

05:24.976 --> 05:27.065
I noticed that you previously
had been on antidepressants.

05:27.239 --> 05:29.329
I stopped taking those
nine months ago.

05:29.503 --> 05:31.418
They didn't help, and I found
an alternative therapy
that's working great.

05:31.592 --> 05:32.636
Wonderful.

05:32.810 --> 05:34.072
Cognitive
behavioral therapy?

05:34.246 --> 05:36.988
Nope. [CHUCKLES]
Uh, I'm injecting
a psilocybin serum

05:37.162 --> 05:38.250
that I make from
hallucinogenic mushrooms

05:38.425 --> 05:39.121
I grow
in my basement.

05:42.559 --> 05:44.431
Okay, that's, uh, crazy.

05:44.605 --> 05:46.084
You need to stop that
immediately.

05:46.258 --> 05:49.218
There's tons of studies online
that show that psilocybin

05:49.392 --> 05:51.916
causes dopamine surges
that treat depression.

05:52.090 --> 05:53.091
And even more studies
that show that people

05:53.265 --> 05:55.180
who self-medicate
with street drugs

05:55.355 --> 05:58.140
end up more depressed,
addicted, and sometimes
even dead.

05:58.314 --> 06:00.447
I spent a year researching
mushroom cultivation

06:00.621 --> 06:02.318
and learning how to
extract the psilocybin.

06:02.492 --> 06:03.885
And most importantly,

06:04.059 --> 06:05.234
this is the first treatment
that's ever worked.

06:06.844 --> 06:07.932
I've never felt better.

06:11.893 --> 06:13.373
At least let me do
some additional tests

06:13.547 --> 06:14.548
to make sure there aren't
any adverse side effects.

06:14.722 --> 06:16.288
Sure.

06:16.463 --> 06:17.420
I'm always open
to new information.

06:18.552 --> 06:20.380
♪♪♪♪

06:25.036 --> 06:27.430
Good morning.
How can I help you?

06:27.604 --> 06:29.127
We're here to camp
at Yosemite Creek.

06:29.301 --> 06:31.216
Great. You have a reservation?

06:31.391 --> 06:32.479
Reservation?

06:32.653 --> 06:33.958
Campsites
are reservation only.

06:35.003 --> 06:36.787
That's not true.

06:36.961 --> 06:39.094
There are 27 first come,
first serve campsites.

06:39.268 --> 06:42.793
There were 27 campsites
at 6:00 a.m.

06:42.967 --> 06:46.797
By 6:45,
they were all taken.

06:46.971 --> 06:48.190
I'm gonna need you
to turn the car around.

06:48.364 --> 06:50.148
No, we need to go camping.

06:50.322 --> 06:52.499
Sir, I understand
you're upset, but...

06:52.673 --> 06:54.414
No. You...
You don't understand
at all why...

06:54.588 --> 06:55.763
Shaun, it's okay.

06:55.937 --> 06:56.633
We'll find another place
to camp.

06:56.807 --> 06:58.940
Uh, thank you.

06:59.114 --> 07:00.463
♪♪♪♪

07:06.338 --> 07:07.427
DR. LIM: Tighten up.

07:07.601 --> 07:09.080
Now work
from the outside in.

07:09.254 --> 07:10.995
Eliminate
any arterial feeders.

07:13.824 --> 07:14.999
This would be
a lot easier

07:15.173 --> 07:16.436
if they'd let me do this
seven years ago.

07:16.610 --> 07:18.133
ASHER: It's not their fault.

07:18.307 --> 07:21.136
They're scared of surgery
for their 12-year-old child.

07:21.310 --> 07:23.007
They're arrogant.
And stubborn.

07:25.140 --> 07:25.880
You're quiet.

07:27.838 --> 07:29.361
CLAIRE: Oh. Sorry.

07:29.536 --> 07:32.539
I was actually thinking
about my own parents.

07:32.713 --> 07:35.542
Miles thinks that we should
"deal with the past"

07:35.716 --> 07:36.847
so that there's not
a barrier between us.

07:38.109 --> 07:39.937
Things have been going
pretty good.

07:40.111 --> 07:41.809
And why
mess with success?

07:41.983 --> 07:43.114
ASHER: I agree.

07:43.288 --> 07:45.029
When it comes to parents,
some things,

07:45.203 --> 07:47.249
in fact, many things,
should just be left unsaid.

07:47.423 --> 07:50.034
DR. LIM: Says the guy
who doesn't have
a relationship with his.

07:50.208 --> 07:53.560
Yeah. Because I said things
that should have been unsaid.

07:53.734 --> 07:55.387
Well, I agree
with Miles.

07:55.562 --> 07:56.911
It's not gonna be
an easy conversation,

07:57.085 --> 07:58.695
but...

07:58.869 --> 08:00.305
Wounds that aren't treated
get worse.

08:03.047 --> 08:04.571
[ALARM BEEPING]ASHER: There's blood
in her ET tube.

08:04.745 --> 08:06.616
CLAIRE: Must be
a bleeder in the airway.

08:06.790 --> 08:08.052
DR. LIM: Retract the wound.

08:08.226 --> 08:11.316
[HOSE SUCKING]

08:11.491 --> 08:13.797
♪♪♪♪

08:13.971 --> 08:15.233
DR. PARK: The research
on psilocybin

08:15.407 --> 08:16.408
for drug-resistant
depression is promising.

08:17.758 --> 08:19.324
Apex of the lungs
look clear.

08:19.499 --> 08:21.370
There's a big difference
between "promising"
and "proven."

08:21.544 --> 08:23.677
Not to mention a drug
made by professionals

08:23.851 --> 08:26.418
versus some guy growing
mushrooms in his basement.

08:26.593 --> 08:28.856
You're the most
skeptical guy I know

08:29.030 --> 08:30.640
about alternative medicine,
but this you agree with?

08:30.814 --> 08:32.555
I'm not surprised.

08:32.729 --> 08:34.252
That Park's
a total hypocrite?

08:34.426 --> 08:35.123
JORDAN: That you two disagree.

08:36.951 --> 08:38.082
You never agree
on anything.

08:39.475 --> 08:40.302
I think you just...

08:41.695 --> 08:44.175
Enjoy arguing
with each other.

08:44.349 --> 08:45.350
[SCOFFS]

08:45.525 --> 08:46.395
You need to get closer.

08:49.224 --> 08:50.486
Can you

08:50.660 --> 08:52.314
focus on the left
inferior lobe?

08:52.488 --> 08:53.837
Uh...

08:54.011 --> 08:55.012
[COMPUTER WARBLES]

08:55.186 --> 08:56.274
What is that?A lesion.

08:56.448 --> 08:57.841
A fungal lesion.

09:00.278 --> 09:01.802
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

09:06.546 --> 09:09.549
♪♪♪♪

09:09.723 --> 09:11.812
This isn't camping.
It's tailgating.

09:11.986 --> 09:12.987
There's trees,

09:13.161 --> 09:14.945
a place we can pitch a tent

09:15.119 --> 09:15.946
and build a fire.

09:19.123 --> 09:20.734
It smells like gasoline.

09:22.257 --> 09:24.215
Oh.

09:24.389 --> 09:27.218
I think their generator
might have a leak.

09:27.392 --> 09:29.525
Just what you want
right next to a campfire.

09:29.699 --> 09:31.701
♪♪♪♪

09:34.530 --> 09:36.140
We have a view
of the lake.

09:37.359 --> 09:38.447
It's pretty, isn't it?

09:39.796 --> 09:41.493
Yeah.

09:41.668 --> 09:43.365
♪♪♪♪

09:46.803 --> 09:48.675
♪♪♪♪

10:04.908 --> 10:07.650
We had to abort the laser
surgery due to a bleed,

10:07.824 --> 10:10.392
but she's conscious and stable
now in post-op recovery.

10:10.566 --> 10:12.829
The AVM infiltrated
too deep into the
upper lobe of the lung

10:13.003 --> 10:14.614
to ablate
with the laser.

10:14.788 --> 10:17.181
We'll have to go back in
and remove her collarbone
for better access.

10:18.052 --> 10:19.444
Another surgery?

10:19.619 --> 10:21.708
To remove her bone?

10:21.882 --> 10:24.275
We'll put it back
after we excise the AVM.

10:24.449 --> 10:26.190
She'll have to wear a brace
until the bone heals.

10:26.364 --> 10:28.976
Vascular malformations
are chameleons.

10:29.150 --> 10:31.108
It's hard to tell
where abnormal
blood vessels end

10:31.282 --> 10:32.501
and normal ones begin.

10:32.675 --> 10:34.372
You were all
a lot more confident

10:34.546 --> 10:36.505
in your assessment
this morning.

10:36.679 --> 10:37.288
We want to take
our daughter home.

10:37.462 --> 10:40.291
Yeah.Now.

10:40.465 --> 10:42.032
I'm sorry.
That's not possible.

10:42.206 --> 10:44.295
The laser surgery caused
weakening in the AVM,

10:44.469 --> 10:45.688
which means
it could rebleed
at any time.

10:45.862 --> 10:47.603
♪♪♪♪

10:51.346 --> 10:53.435
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

10:53.609 --> 10:54.915
Okay.

10:55.089 --> 10:57.526
♪♪♪♪

10:58.832 --> 11:01.573
Okay.

11:01.748 --> 11:03.488
You're lucky. If you scheduled
your physical a week later,

11:03.663 --> 11:05.186
your liver and lungs
would be failing.

11:05.360 --> 11:07.144
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

11:07.318 --> 11:09.407
And after the surgery?

11:09.581 --> 11:11.192
What about
my depression?

11:11.366 --> 11:14.108
You're asking if you can
continue a treatment
that's killing you?

11:14.282 --> 11:16.284
[SIGHS]

11:16.458 --> 11:19.722
Before I started
the psilocybin injections...

11:19.896 --> 11:21.158
I was miserable.

11:21.332 --> 11:25.946
I-I couldn't sleep,
I barely ate.

11:26.120 --> 11:29.253
I can't bear to face
that darkness again.

11:33.736 --> 11:37.914
I don't know
if it's the psilocybin
or placebo effect,

11:38.088 --> 11:40.525
or something else
neither of us understands,

11:42.745 --> 11:43.746
but if you found
the light once...

11:45.922 --> 11:47.576
You can find it again.

11:47.750 --> 11:49.491
♪♪♪♪

11:56.150 --> 11:58.456
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

11:58.630 --> 12:00.763
♪♪♪♪

12:05.420 --> 12:06.726
Okay.

12:06.900 --> 12:07.857
It's a nice fire.

12:10.251 --> 12:11.513
I used
the Teepee method.

12:20.696 --> 12:22.611
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

12:22.785 --> 12:25.309
♪♪♪♪

12:30.227 --> 12:33.317
I'm thinking open thoracotomy
and midline laparotomy.

12:33.491 --> 12:35.624
We might be able to
use minimally
invasive scope surgery

12:35.798 --> 12:37.147
to get the big lesions
and attack the rest

12:37.321 --> 12:38.496
post-operatively
with anti-fungals.

12:38.670 --> 12:40.760
More like
minimally effective.

12:40.934 --> 12:42.892
Better to be aggressive,
take them all out at once.

12:43.066 --> 12:44.807
That's a huge operation
with a long, painful recovery.

12:44.981 --> 12:46.504
He has a huge problem.

12:46.678 --> 12:48.985
This lesion looks like
it extends behind the liver.

12:52.772 --> 12:54.686
You're the senior
surgical resident.

12:54.861 --> 12:57.080
You need to start making
these calls.

12:57.254 --> 12:58.342
JORDAN: I'm not so sure
about that.

13:02.042 --> 13:04.871
I'm sorry, but I question
Dr. Park's objectivity

13:05.045 --> 13:07.047
when it comes
to Dr. Reznick's ideas.

13:07.221 --> 13:09.092
I don't care where
an idea comes from,

13:09.266 --> 13:10.311
and I don't appreciate you
accusing me...

13:10.485 --> 13:11.486
It wasn't an accusation.

13:11.660 --> 13:12.661
Then what
would you call it?

13:12.835 --> 13:15.229
A respectful
and sincere question.

13:17.448 --> 13:18.362
What's the answer?

13:21.713 --> 13:23.672
My objective opinion is...

13:25.848 --> 13:27.154
A minimally invasive approach
is best.

13:29.417 --> 13:32.159
Okay.

13:32.333 --> 13:35.771
I want it all mapped out with
a 3D reconstruction simulation
before we go in there.

13:35.945 --> 13:37.642
We'll operate
in the morning.

13:37.817 --> 13:39.557
[RAIN FALLING]

13:39.731 --> 13:41.646
♪♪♪♪

13:44.867 --> 13:45.650
It's actually
kinda soothing.

13:48.871 --> 13:52.309
It reminds me
of the dripping faucet
in our old apartment.

13:52.483 --> 13:53.267
The sound
helped me fall asleep.

13:53.441 --> 13:54.398
Mm.

13:55.922 --> 13:57.010
I loved that building.

13:58.489 --> 13:59.664
It's where
we had our first hug.

13:59.839 --> 14:00.927
[GLASS SHATTERS]

14:01.101 --> 14:02.667
MAN 1: Oh![MAN 2 LAUGHS]

14:02.842 --> 14:04.408
Definitely not soothing.

14:09.805 --> 14:10.850
[GRUNTS]

14:11.024 --> 14:12.416
These might help.

14:14.114 --> 14:16.246
You brought earplugs
to a camping trip?

14:17.508 --> 14:17.944
Sometimes you snore.

14:19.728 --> 14:20.685
Thank you.

14:23.558 --> 14:24.864
LEA: Mm.

14:25.038 --> 14:26.169
Mm.

14:30.521 --> 14:31.696
Mm.

14:36.310 --> 14:37.964
Mm! Ooh!

14:38.138 --> 14:39.182
[GASPS]

14:40.357 --> 14:42.359
[INHALES SHARPLY]

14:42.533 --> 14:43.534
[SIGHS]

14:45.972 --> 14:47.060
That's it.

14:47.234 --> 14:48.017
I give up.

14:49.889 --> 14:52.239
I have a repair kit.

14:52.413 --> 14:53.370
I don't want to
fix things, Shaun.

14:53.544 --> 14:54.458
I just want to go home.

14:57.287 --> 14:57.940
I...

15:00.551 --> 15:03.598
Don't want to go home.

15:03.772 --> 15:06.470
If you want to stay
in a cold, wet, leaky tent,
go ahead,

15:06.644 --> 15:07.471
but I am sleeping
in the car.

15:24.532 --> 15:26.142
[SIGHS]

15:26.316 --> 15:27.491
Ah.

15:27.665 --> 15:30.146
29:32.

15:30.320 --> 15:33.236
Yeah. I used to do sub-25
on recovery days.

15:33.410 --> 15:35.804
Hey, you have time to grab
a quick bite before you go in?

15:39.634 --> 15:41.114
I was actually
thinking, uh...

15:42.376 --> 15:43.551
Maybe we could talk.

15:45.379 --> 15:46.641
I would love that.

15:46.815 --> 15:48.686
[SIGHS]

15:48.860 --> 15:50.514
♪♪♪♪

15:59.436 --> 16:01.221
The last time I saw you
before you left,

16:03.179 --> 16:05.921
I... I screamed at you

16:06.095 --> 16:07.314
because you missed
my birthday party,

16:09.185 --> 16:11.883
and for the longest time,

16:12.058 --> 16:15.800
I thought if I could just
tell you I was sorry,

16:15.975 --> 16:16.845
that you'd come back.

16:20.588 --> 16:22.416
It wasn't you, Claire.

16:22.590 --> 16:24.244
None of it.

16:24.418 --> 16:25.810
I mean, you...

16:25.985 --> 16:28.074
Were a great kid.

16:28.248 --> 16:30.815
So smart
and thoughtful.

16:32.948 --> 16:34.341
How could you
just disappear?

16:38.780 --> 16:40.564
Things between
your mother and I
were such a mess.

16:43.263 --> 16:46.570
One night, she was having
one of her episodes,

16:48.790 --> 16:52.098
told me I was worthless.

16:54.839 --> 16:57.581
The only thing
I was good for
was money.

16:57.755 --> 16:59.061
♪♪♪♪

17:01.498 --> 17:03.848
I said, "Okay,
if that's all you want,

17:04.023 --> 17:05.241
"that's all I'mma give you."

17:05.415 --> 17:07.417
I sent her a check
every month.

17:07.591 --> 17:09.332
Never saw
or spoke to her again.

17:11.987 --> 17:14.163
It was mean
and petty.

17:16.252 --> 17:17.253
Pathetic.

17:17.427 --> 17:18.602
We never got any money.

17:20.735 --> 17:22.693
What are you
talking about?

17:22.867 --> 17:25.609
I sent monthly support
until you finished college.

17:27.524 --> 17:29.613
I worked two jobs.

17:29.787 --> 17:33.922
I took out a loan to pay
for tuition and our rent.

17:34.096 --> 17:35.619
♪♪♪♪

17:39.971 --> 17:43.323
Look... I sent
more than enough for rent,

17:43.497 --> 17:45.803
for clothes, for food.

17:45.977 --> 17:48.545
She stole my money
from my child.

17:48.719 --> 17:50.286
The child
you totally abandoned.

17:50.460 --> 17:52.201
No. Not totally.

17:52.375 --> 17:54.203
It's not my fault
she squandered that money.

17:54.377 --> 17:56.423
It's not your fault I grew up
without a father?

17:58.120 --> 17:59.469
Without any social life

17:59.643 --> 18:02.646
because I was so busy
being a mom to my own mom?

18:02.820 --> 18:04.866
The woman that
you walked out on

18:05.040 --> 18:06.563
when things
stopped being fun?

18:06.737 --> 18:08.043
Okay, listen,
I'm sorry, okay?

18:08.217 --> 18:09.349
I didn't mean for this
to become an argument.

18:09.523 --> 18:11.394
No, you're not sorry.

18:11.568 --> 18:14.005
If you were, you wouldn't
still be blaming her,
using her as an excuse.

18:14.180 --> 18:17.661
♪♪♪♪

18:17.835 --> 18:20.969
You took off
because you were too weak

18:21.143 --> 18:23.754
to do what a father
is supposed to do...

18:23.928 --> 18:25.930
To take care of me,
to protect me.

18:28.107 --> 18:30.196
And now you're back
when it's easy,

18:30.370 --> 18:31.632
when I don't need
a father?

18:31.806 --> 18:33.373
♪♪♪♪

18:35.157 --> 18:37.072
No, you know what?
Forget it.

18:37.246 --> 18:38.334
Claire...Look, just don't...

18:38.508 --> 18:39.814
Don't call,
don't come to the door.

18:39.988 --> 18:41.555
Just leave me alone.

18:41.729 --> 18:43.209
♪♪♪♪

18:47.952 --> 18:50.172
♪♪♪♪

18:54.263 --> 18:55.699
[SIGHS]

19:01.444 --> 19:03.359
[BIRD SQUAWKING]

19:03.533 --> 19:05.535
♪♪♪♪

19:28.254 --> 19:29.516
I thought
this would be helpful.

19:31.605 --> 19:32.345
I was wrong.

19:34.564 --> 19:36.218
We can go home.

19:38.873 --> 19:41.092
Well...

19:41.267 --> 19:42.746
Why don't we do the hike
you planned first?

19:46.141 --> 19:48.752
Is that what you want?

19:50.363 --> 19:51.668
Is that what you want?

19:51.842 --> 19:53.192
Mm.

19:53.366 --> 19:55.237
I think so.

19:56.586 --> 19:57.979
♪♪♪♪

19:59.763 --> 20:01.156
Okay.

20:01.330 --> 20:02.897
New plan.

20:03.071 --> 20:06.596
Blueberry pancakes,
and then hike,

20:06.770 --> 20:09.120
and then back home
to our warm and cozy
and dry bed.

20:15.779 --> 20:17.477
DR. LIM: Divide the sternal
attachment of the SCM.

20:20.175 --> 20:22.569
ASHER: And done.

20:22.743 --> 20:24.005
CLAIRE: Removing
the medial clavicle.

20:26.268 --> 20:27.269
You have the talk?

20:29.184 --> 20:30.533
Yeah.

20:30.707 --> 20:32.274
I never said
it would be easy.

20:32.448 --> 20:34.885
You can't excise a tumor
without some bleeding.

20:35.059 --> 20:36.800
Some tumors are inoperable.

20:39.107 --> 20:40.456
He wants to be forgiven.

20:41.892 --> 20:43.807
I... I just can't.

20:46.157 --> 20:47.028
ASHER: He doesn't deserve it.

20:49.813 --> 20:54.296
Well, it's not the kid's job
to make the parents
feel good about themselves.

20:54.470 --> 20:56.342
This mat of vessels
is invading
the upper lung tissue.

20:56.516 --> 20:58.909
How deep does it go
on your end?

20:59.083 --> 21:00.389
ASHER: I can see
underneath the apex,

21:00.563 --> 21:04.437
but can't tell what's tumor
and what's subclavian artery.

21:04.611 --> 21:05.829
We can't get this out
without pulling out

21:06.003 --> 21:08.267
the whole upper lobe
of her lung.

21:08.441 --> 21:09.920
ASHER: Well, the parents
are not gonna like that.

21:10.094 --> 21:10.921
I-I'll go.

21:12.183 --> 21:13.359
They don't trust you.

21:13.533 --> 21:14.751
Well, that's
not your problem.

21:14.925 --> 21:16.362
Well, it shouldn't be
the patient's either.

21:16.536 --> 21:18.842
I'll have a better chance
of getting their consent.

21:33.944 --> 21:34.858
I bought some pastries.

21:35.903 --> 21:36.904
Uh, I'm good.

21:44.433 --> 21:45.521
[SIGHS]

21:47.218 --> 21:48.655
I, uh... I'm sorry
that I, uh...

21:50.134 --> 21:52.441
Unloaded the gun
without telling you.

21:55.052 --> 21:56.880
Thank you.

21:57.054 --> 21:58.882
I, uh...
I appreciate that.

22:01.407 --> 22:03.713
I know
that you're nervous
around guns,

22:03.887 --> 22:05.411
which is
all the more reason

22:05.585 --> 22:08.065
that you should
just leave mine alone.

22:08.239 --> 22:10.198
Well, maybe
there's a better way
to deal with this.

22:10.372 --> 22:14.724
So, w-what if we kept
your gun in your nightstand
like always,

22:14.898 --> 22:16.683
but we keep the ammunition
in another room?

22:18.598 --> 22:22.036
So your idea of a compromise
is that I agree to do

22:22.210 --> 22:25.126
what you've been doing
behind my back all along?

22:25.300 --> 22:27.737
An intruder is not
gonna wait for me

22:27.911 --> 22:30.436
to collect my bullets
from the guest room closet.

22:30.610 --> 22:32.612
My house is not that big.

22:32.786 --> 22:33.395
I don't...
I'm so confused.

22:33.569 --> 22:34.831
You still have to
run up the stairs

22:35.005 --> 22:35.919
and get the thing
either way.

22:38.095 --> 22:40.663
Do you ever notice
that whenever we're talking

22:40.837 --> 22:44.363
about something
related to the home
that we both share,

22:44.537 --> 22:48.410
that you always refer to it
as your house?

22:48.584 --> 22:49.585
I do?

22:50.934 --> 22:53.720
This isn't
about gun safety.

22:53.894 --> 22:56.679
This is about your house
and your rules

22:56.853 --> 22:58.594
and your wanting
to control me.

22:58.768 --> 23:01.728
You don't trust me to make
decisions about my own life.

23:01.902 --> 23:03.643
I'm just trying to find a way
to make you feel safe.

23:03.817 --> 23:07.995
I-I don't need you
or any other man

23:08.169 --> 23:09.779
to find a way
to make me feel safe.

23:18.571 --> 23:21.225
♪♪♪♪

23:21.400 --> 23:23.010
LEA: Oh, thank you.

23:23.184 --> 23:24.838
[LEA SIGHS]

23:25.012 --> 23:26.666
♪♪♪♪

23:34.891 --> 23:36.415
It's actually pretty
outside the campground.

23:38.417 --> 23:40.201
Another half-mile,
and we can see the lake.

23:41.898 --> 23:42.986
You're really cute.

23:43.160 --> 23:44.640
I want
to take a picture.

23:44.814 --> 23:45.685
Go stand on that log.

23:47.338 --> 23:49.166
I'll get you
from a low angle.

23:49.340 --> 23:51.255
A hero angle
because you're my hero.

23:51.430 --> 23:52.735
[CHUCKLES]

23:56.652 --> 23:57.523
Okay.

23:59.263 --> 24:00.264
Okay, a smidge
to the left.

24:04.878 --> 24:05.835
Aah! Ah![GASPS]

24:06.009 --> 24:07.010
Shaun!

24:08.359 --> 24:09.273
Are you okay?

24:11.711 --> 24:13.713
Oh, my God.
You are not okay.

24:13.887 --> 24:16.455
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

24:16.629 --> 24:18.631
♪♪♪♪

24:22.939 --> 24:25.028
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

24:26.682 --> 24:28.945
Okay. On the count of three.

24:29.119 --> 24:30.686
Mm-hmm.Ready?

24:30.860 --> 24:32.209
One, two...

24:32.383 --> 24:34.081
[BONES CRACK]Aah! Ah!

24:34.255 --> 24:36.083
You were supposed to wait
until I got to three!

24:36.257 --> 24:37.345
I know,
but in the movies,

24:37.519 --> 24:39.521
they always go early
to catch you off guard.

24:39.695 --> 24:40.827
You don't need the element
of surprise

24:41.001 --> 24:42.132
to reduce
a dislocated ankle.

24:42.306 --> 24:42.655
Okay,
but did it work?

24:45.571 --> 24:46.267
Yes.

24:47.224 --> 24:48.095
You...

24:49.488 --> 24:51.315
You relocated it
correctly.

24:52.926 --> 24:54.580
Damn.

24:54.754 --> 24:55.972
But...

24:56.146 --> 24:57.931
My toes are still
dusky and numb.

25:00.020 --> 25:01.543
The posterior
tibial artery's torn.

25:03.806 --> 25:05.808
I thought
it was just pinched.

25:05.982 --> 25:07.114
If circulation
isn't restored,

25:07.288 --> 25:08.898
I'll have
permanent tissue damage,

25:09.072 --> 25:10.552
maybe even have
to have my foot amputated.

25:13.381 --> 25:14.817
This is not a problem.

25:14.991 --> 25:17.472
I can run to where I can get
a cell signal and call 911.

25:17.646 --> 25:19.300
It'll take
at least two hours

25:19.474 --> 25:20.562
for you to run back
to the campground.

25:20.736 --> 25:22.608
I'm faster than I look.

25:22.782 --> 25:25.262
You told me you used
to skip phys-ed class
because you hated running.

25:25.436 --> 25:26.699
I can hate it
and still be good at it.

25:26.873 --> 25:27.656
No.

25:31.051 --> 25:34.054
My pocket knife
is as sharp as a scalpel.

25:34.228 --> 25:35.751
The tent repair kit
has nylon thread,

25:35.925 --> 25:38.058
and you can use a fishhook
as a suturing needle.

25:38.232 --> 25:39.842
You are
obviously delirious

25:40.016 --> 25:41.627
because there's no way in hell
I am doing surgery.

25:41.801 --> 25:43.150
It's not
a complicated procedure.

25:43.324 --> 25:45.413
For a surgeon,
which I'm not!

25:45.587 --> 25:47.763
I'll guide you
step-by-step, okay?

25:47.937 --> 25:48.851
It'll just take
two sutures.

25:49.025 --> 25:50.331
I've seen you hem
your pants.

25:50.505 --> 25:52.812
An artery
is not a pair of jeans!

25:52.986 --> 25:54.117
There's a bottle of tequila
in my backpack.

25:56.772 --> 25:57.947
You will need to sterilize
the incision,

25:58.121 --> 25:59.558
and I will need
anesthesia.

25:59.732 --> 26:00.646
Shaun, I...

26:00.820 --> 26:01.821
Tequila! Stat!

26:03.474 --> 26:05.651
We thought
you were certain before.

26:05.825 --> 26:07.653
I know you're scared
and this is confusing.

26:07.827 --> 26:11.439
We brought her in
with some minor inflammation.

26:11.613 --> 26:12.875
No, the inflammation
was not minor.

26:16.139 --> 26:18.315
What we are proposing
would reduce
her lung capacity,

26:18.489 --> 26:20.666
but she can still live
a normal life.

26:20.840 --> 26:22.319
No. No, we're taking her
someplace else.

26:22.493 --> 26:23.669
We're gonna get
a second opinion.

26:23.843 --> 26:25.932
We can't cut out part
of our daughter's lung.

26:27.368 --> 26:28.674
She'd never forgive us.

26:28.848 --> 26:29.892
[SIGHS]

26:32.068 --> 26:33.200
And maybe she shouldn't.

26:37.160 --> 26:38.945
You were wrong
to refuse the surgery

26:39.119 --> 26:42.252
that Dr. Lim proposed
years ago.

26:42.426 --> 26:45.473
A-Are you trying to guilt us
into agreeing with you?

26:46.605 --> 26:49.651
You are guilty.

26:49.825 --> 26:52.611
Ava is in this situation
because you were too afraid
to make a tough decision,

26:52.785 --> 26:55.744
and now you are trying
to blame everyone else

26:55.918 --> 26:57.790
because you can't deal
with the guilt of having
messed up.

27:02.925 --> 27:06.015
You need to stop thinking
about what is gonna make you
feel like a good parent

27:06.189 --> 27:08.278
and start thinking about
what your daughter needs.

27:08.452 --> 27:10.803
♪♪♪♪

27:24.904 --> 27:26.079
Careful
with that anesthesia.

27:26.253 --> 27:27.907
I need you coherent enough
to guide me through this.

27:28.081 --> 27:29.517
Don't worry.

27:29.691 --> 27:31.519
I've calculated
the proper dosage.

27:31.693 --> 27:32.825
N-No.

27:32.999 --> 27:34.827
No, not like that.

27:35.001 --> 27:37.786
The scalpel goes
on the left of the tray,
sponges on the right,

27:37.960 --> 27:39.396
needle driver and sutures
in the middle.

27:39.570 --> 27:40.702
Okay. Got it.

27:42.138 --> 27:43.574
Okay.

27:43.749 --> 27:45.272
And might I suggest
not barking instructions
at me?

27:45.446 --> 27:46.752
I'm freaked out enough
already.

27:46.926 --> 27:49.842
I'll do my best.

27:50.016 --> 27:52.061
But even with the tequila,
when you cut into my ankle,

27:52.235 --> 27:54.020
I'll be in extreme pain,
which can cause irritability.

27:55.412 --> 27:56.370
I can't do this.

27:56.544 --> 27:58.067
You have to.

27:58.241 --> 28:00.766
The worst that could happen
is you mess it up

28:00.940 --> 28:03.029
and cause permanent damage
to my foot,

28:03.203 --> 28:04.770
which is exactly what will
happen if you don't do it.

28:06.075 --> 28:07.598
[SIGHS] Okay.

28:07.773 --> 28:09.252
Tequila. Stat.

28:09.426 --> 28:10.732
♪♪♪♪

28:14.867 --> 28:16.782
[MONITOR BEEPING]

28:16.956 --> 28:17.870
DR. ANDREWS: Suction.

28:19.741 --> 28:20.263
JORDAN: That enough?

28:21.438 --> 28:22.701
Perfect.

28:22.875 --> 28:24.790
Mediastinum's cleared.

28:24.964 --> 28:27.444
Now onto the lung lesions.

28:27.618 --> 28:29.838
DR. PARK: I'm having
a problem
maneuvering in here.

28:30.012 --> 28:32.972
There's too much
peritoneal scarring
from the fungal deposits.

28:33.146 --> 28:34.582
DR. ANDREWS: Can you
cut at it sharply?

28:34.756 --> 28:35.496
I'm too close
to the common bile duct.

28:36.366 --> 28:37.280
Need help?

28:40.370 --> 28:41.154
Morgan was right.

28:44.418 --> 28:45.854
There's no way to remove all
the lesions laparoscopically.

28:48.291 --> 28:50.598
All right,
let's pull the scopes
and open him up.

28:50.772 --> 28:52.078
♪♪♪♪

28:55.472 --> 28:56.778
[SHAUN BREATHING HEAVILY]

28:56.952 --> 28:58.780
[LEA SIGHS]

28:58.954 --> 29:00.303
♪♪♪♪

29:03.959 --> 29:05.352
[GRUNTS]

29:05.526 --> 29:07.006
Okay, the blood's pouring out.

29:07.180 --> 29:08.268
What do I do now?

29:08.442 --> 29:09.530
Okay.

29:09.704 --> 29:11.532
Okay, tighten the tourniquet

29:11.706 --> 29:13.752
and then use a sponge
to clear the blood.

29:13.926 --> 29:14.796
♪♪♪♪

29:17.233 --> 29:18.844
[SIGHS] Okay.

29:20.759 --> 29:21.411
It's clearing up.

29:23.022 --> 29:25.328
You should be able
to see...

29:25.502 --> 29:27.417
I see it.
And the leaking hole.

29:27.591 --> 29:30.333
Now you just need to use
the needle driver

29:30.507 --> 29:31.726
to sew
the edges together.

29:33.162 --> 29:33.946
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

29:34.120 --> 29:34.903
Be careful not...

29:37.210 --> 29:38.341
Be c-careful
not to what?

29:41.040 --> 29:41.823
Shaun?

29:43.694 --> 29:45.871
Put the backpack
under my head.

29:46.045 --> 29:46.741
How's that gonna help
with your ankle?

29:46.915 --> 29:48.569
It...won't,

29:48.743 --> 29:50.919
but I'm about to lose
consciousness from blood loss,

29:51.093 --> 29:54.662
and I don't
want dirt in my...

29:56.098 --> 29:56.795
Shaun?

29:57.970 --> 29:58.709
Shaun?

30:00.407 --> 30:01.364
Shaun.

30:01.538 --> 30:02.844
Shaun.

30:03.018 --> 30:03.889
Shaun.

30:08.197 --> 30:10.504
Shaun. Shaun, come on.

30:10.678 --> 30:11.592
Come on, Shaun.

30:11.766 --> 30:12.811
Shaun.

30:13.812 --> 30:14.900
Oh.

30:17.728 --> 30:18.773
Okay.

30:18.947 --> 30:21.732
[SIGHS]

30:21.907 --> 30:24.648
Come on, Lea.
If you can hem a pant leg,
apparently you can do this.

30:26.912 --> 30:28.261
All right.

30:28.435 --> 30:29.349
Okay.

30:29.523 --> 30:31.177
♪♪♪♪

30:39.315 --> 30:41.535
CLAIRE: I have freed
the pleural membrane.

30:41.709 --> 30:44.407
[MONITOR BEEPING]

30:44.581 --> 30:46.409
♪♪♪♪

30:49.412 --> 30:51.893
Oh, why does blood have
to be so damn slippery?

30:53.025 --> 30:54.243
♪♪♪♪

30:56.071 --> 30:58.117
[SIGHS]

30:58.291 --> 31:00.510
And how am I supposed
to tie a knot

31:00.684 --> 31:03.209
if I can't even grip
the damn thread?

31:10.607 --> 31:12.087
Mm.

31:12.261 --> 31:14.785
There we go.
There we go.

31:14.960 --> 31:15.917
Okay.

31:17.527 --> 31:18.441
Okay.

31:20.226 --> 31:21.967
Here we go.

31:23.490 --> 31:24.708
Mm.

31:24.883 --> 31:26.710
♪♪♪♪

31:34.544 --> 31:35.502
You're a woman.

31:38.070 --> 31:38.722
Um, yup.

31:41.334 --> 31:44.685
I've always considered myself
a supporter of women,

31:44.859 --> 31:47.601
you know, equal pay
for equal work,

31:47.775 --> 31:49.777
the right to choose.

31:49.951 --> 31:51.474
Uh, thank you,
from all of us.

31:55.435 --> 31:57.089
Debbie seems to think
that I am...

32:00.005 --> 32:02.703
Overbearing
and, uh, controlling.

32:06.663 --> 32:08.013
[SIGHS]

32:12.452 --> 32:16.717
My ex
was a humanities professor
and ACLU chapter head.

32:16.891 --> 32:20.808
But I made more money,
and I don't think
he was conscious of this,

32:20.982 --> 32:22.375
but I do feel
he was threatened by...

32:23.942 --> 32:25.465
My independence.

32:25.639 --> 32:26.988
The more insecure he got,

32:27.162 --> 32:28.772
the more controlling
he became.

32:28.947 --> 32:31.210
He had to pick
the restaurants
where we ate,

32:31.384 --> 32:32.385
the movies we saw.

32:34.648 --> 32:36.737
I mean, I definitely had
my own issues, but...

32:39.174 --> 32:42.003
His need to control me
was one of the many reasons
our marriage fell apart.

32:42.177 --> 32:44.527
♪♪♪♪

32:55.190 --> 32:56.148
[SIGHS]

33:03.416 --> 33:05.157
I can feel my toes.

33:08.290 --> 33:09.596
Are you finished?

33:12.381 --> 33:13.556
No.

33:13.730 --> 33:14.557
[SIGHS]

33:19.084 --> 33:20.563
Now I'm finished.

33:20.737 --> 33:21.608
[SIGHS]

33:26.656 --> 33:28.484
There's enough flow
to keep the tissue alive

33:28.658 --> 33:29.398
until we get to an ER.

33:31.922 --> 33:33.228
You did this
with a tent repair kit?

33:33.402 --> 33:34.621
And a fishhook.

33:36.405 --> 33:38.668
She is very good
at fixing things.

33:40.670 --> 33:41.367
You're lucky.

33:43.673 --> 33:44.370
Yes.

33:45.719 --> 33:46.720
I am.

33:46.894 --> 33:48.069
♪♪♪♪

33:51.986 --> 33:53.770
How do you feel?

33:53.944 --> 33:56.208
Like a gutted fish.

33:56.382 --> 33:57.731
I'm sorry.
We had no choice
but to open you up

33:57.905 --> 33:59.254
to access all the lesions.

33:59.428 --> 34:00.734
DR. REZNICK: But they were
able to remove them all

34:00.908 --> 34:02.344
without damaging
any of the organs.

34:02.518 --> 34:03.998
You should recover fully.

34:04.172 --> 34:06.174
Physically.

34:06.348 --> 34:09.438
There are new antidepressants
you haven't tried.

34:09.612 --> 34:11.571
But I also wouldn't stop
the mushroom cultivation.

34:11.745 --> 34:12.615
Really?

34:14.835 --> 34:16.097
After all this?

34:16.271 --> 34:17.794
Cultivation.

34:17.968 --> 34:19.448
If this helped you,

34:19.622 --> 34:21.407
it was either
the placebo effect,

34:21.581 --> 34:24.540
or all the focus you put
into perfecting the process.

34:24.714 --> 34:27.195
Sometimes distraction
is the best medicine.

34:27.369 --> 34:29.458
♪♪♪♪

34:36.117 --> 34:38.032
♪♪♪♪

34:43.690 --> 34:45.083
MURRAY: Hey.

34:45.257 --> 34:47.172
♪♪♪♪

34:48.477 --> 34:49.870
We are...

34:50.044 --> 34:50.697
So sorry.

34:52.568 --> 34:54.222
[EXHALES SHARPLY]This is our fault.

34:59.184 --> 35:00.446
It's okay.

35:04.537 --> 35:05.538
I love you.

35:07.801 --> 35:09.150
[SIGHS]

35:09.324 --> 35:11.935
♪♪♪♪

35:17.158 --> 35:19.204
♪♪♪♪

35:25.427 --> 35:28.778
I thought our relationship
was just a fun distraction,

35:30.824 --> 35:31.955
but when you
pushed me away...

35:34.958 --> 35:36.264
I realized
it was more than that.

35:38.745 --> 35:40.355
I was hurt.

35:40.529 --> 35:41.269
Resentful.

35:43.706 --> 35:45.230
Which made every interaction
we had...

35:46.883 --> 35:47.710
Complicated.

35:50.278 --> 35:51.497
What're you
talking about?

35:51.671 --> 35:54.282
You made sure it wasn't
complicated at all.

35:54.456 --> 35:55.718
We stopped having sex,
and now we're friends.

35:55.892 --> 35:57.894
[BOOT ZIPS]

35:58.068 --> 35:59.200
You know
it's more than that.

36:00.984 --> 36:02.682
And it can't be.

36:02.856 --> 36:03.726
Not anymore.

36:05.119 --> 36:07.556
What does that even mean?

36:07.730 --> 36:09.819
We still work together.
We have to talk
to each other.

36:09.993 --> 36:10.733
About work.
That's it.

36:13.040 --> 36:15.303
We can't try to
keep some sort of
friendship going.

36:15.477 --> 36:17.523
Which means no more jokes,
no more teasing,

36:17.697 --> 36:18.785
nothing that isn't
totally professional.

36:20.134 --> 36:22.005
So, what? We just...

36:22.180 --> 36:23.833
Act like robots
around each other?

36:29.099 --> 36:29.796
I don't want that.

36:32.015 --> 36:32.973
It's boring.

36:36.150 --> 36:37.064
No.

36:39.153 --> 36:41.851
We act like we did
before we ever
moved in together

36:42.025 --> 36:43.418
and let ourselves
get into this...

36:45.203 --> 36:45.812
Unprofessional...

36:47.117 --> 36:47.814
Mess.

36:48.989 --> 36:50.382
Yeah.

36:50.556 --> 36:51.861
Pretending that
what happened
didn't happen.

36:52.035 --> 36:53.080
That always works.

36:56.170 --> 36:56.866
[BOOT ZIPS]

36:57.040 --> 36:58.825
♪♪♪♪

37:06.441 --> 37:08.661
[SIGHS]

37:08.835 --> 37:11.403
♪♪♪♪

37:18.714 --> 37:19.759
[SIGHS]

37:19.933 --> 37:21.195
You were
a horrible father.

37:23.284 --> 37:24.416
And you can't undo
the harm you did.

37:27.984 --> 37:29.029
But...

37:29.203 --> 37:30.335
I should forgive you.

37:33.163 --> 37:33.816
You deserve it.

37:35.470 --> 37:36.341
And I need it.

37:39.474 --> 37:40.475
Because I need you.

37:40.649 --> 37:42.303
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

37:44.479 --> 37:48.483
So, I-I'd like to keep
spending time together...

37:50.180 --> 37:51.138
And talking.

37:55.708 --> 37:56.578
I would love that.

37:59.929 --> 38:00.843
Do you think...

38:03.759 --> 38:04.847
Think maybe
we could, uh...

38:06.762 --> 38:08.851
Restart everything
with a...

38:11.376 --> 38:12.072
Hug?

38:13.247 --> 38:14.944
♪♪♪♪

38:17.860 --> 38:20.298
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

38:20.472 --> 38:22.865
♪♪♪♪

38:32.310 --> 38:33.572
[SIGHS]

38:42.189 --> 38:43.190
I was wrong.

38:46.802 --> 38:48.935
I convinced myself
that I was right,
and I was wrong.

38:53.069 --> 38:54.767
I took...

38:54.941 --> 38:56.116
A choice away from you.

38:59.859 --> 39:03.906
And I will do everything
I can to make it right.

39:07.954 --> 39:09.912
I-I'm...

39:10.086 --> 39:11.261
I'm so sorry.

39:14.656 --> 39:16.919
You don't have
to a-apologize.
Can you stop doing that?

39:27.365 --> 39:29.541
I don't think
I can make this work.

39:31.456 --> 39:35.024
I have had this feeling
for months.

39:35.198 --> 39:36.591
It's like a pit
in my stomach,

39:36.765 --> 39:40.421
and I-I-I didn't want
to...face what it was,

39:40.595 --> 39:43.468
but when we were fighting,

39:43.642 --> 39:47.776
I just felt, like, relief,
like I had an out.

39:47.950 --> 39:49.038
You think
I don't respect you.

39:49.212 --> 39:49.996
I don't...

39:51.563 --> 39:53.391
I do.

39:53.565 --> 39:56.219
Aaron, you almost walked
out of our wedding
because...

39:57.656 --> 39:58.961
I used bad grammar.

40:03.792 --> 40:04.402
That was bad.

40:04.576 --> 40:05.446
[SCOFFS]

40:07.622 --> 40:08.623
That was a bad moment.

40:11.234 --> 40:14.977
Marriages are made up
of moments, right?

40:15.151 --> 40:16.892
So many of our moments
are... Are just...

40:17.066 --> 40:18.067
Are great.

40:21.201 --> 40:23.072
[SIGHS] Too many are so...

40:23.246 --> 40:24.900
Just painful.

40:25.074 --> 40:31.516
♪♪ And I will hold you tight...

40:31.690 --> 40:32.517
This is crazy.

40:34.083 --> 40:34.780
We love each other.

40:37.696 --> 40:38.436
I love you.

40:40.612 --> 40:43.963
♪♪ ...will keep you warm

40:44.137 --> 40:45.965
♪♪ I will build...

40:46.139 --> 40:49.403
I love you so much.

40:49.577 --> 40:51.927
♪♪ And I'll build a fire...

40:52.101 --> 40:54.016
It's just not enough.

40:56.584 --> 40:58.760
♪♪ And in our hearts

40:58.934 --> 41:01.415
♪♪ We still pray for sons
and daughters

41:03.548 --> 41:06.551
♪♪ And all those evenings
out in the garden

41:06.725 --> 41:08.030
♪♪ With red, red wine

41:10.206 --> 41:15.516
♪♪ These quiet hours
turning to years...

41:15.690 --> 41:16.735
Thank you.

41:17.866 --> 41:19.346
♪♪♪♪

41:22.741 --> 41:25.308
The rain, the drunks,

41:25.483 --> 41:28.007
the freezing cold night
alone in my car,

41:28.181 --> 41:29.791
and you almost losing
your foot

41:29.965 --> 41:32.446
was definitely a bit more
of a distraction

41:32.620 --> 41:34.230
than I was hoping for.

41:34.404 --> 41:36.058
♪♪♪♪

41:38.670 --> 41:40.367
But I'm really glad
you took me camping.

41:42.108 --> 41:43.936
♪♪♪♪

41:44.110 --> 41:45.067
You're welcome.

41:48.636 --> 41:50.333
♪♪ And I'll build a fire

41:50.508 --> 41:52.597
♪♪ You fetch the water,
and I'll lay the table

41:54.773 --> 41:56.818
♪♪ And in our hearts

41:56.992 --> 42:01.344
♪♪ We still pray for sons
and daughters

42:01.519 --> 42:04.565
♪♪ And all those evenings
out in the garden

42:04.739 --> 42:06.088
♪♪ With red, red wine

42:08.090 --> 42:14.401
♪♪ These quiet hours
turning to years ♪♪

